    "body": "It is so strange. In our package.json i changed \"instantsearch.js\": \"2.0.2\" to \"instantsearch.js\": \"^2.0.2\". Then i made npm update. In our app.js we have:\r\n`window.$ = require('jquery');\r\nwindow.instantsearch = require('instantsearch.js');`\r\n\r\nIf i start the app we ware getting Reference Errors like \"ReferenceError: $ is not defined\" to this line \"$(function()\" in a different JS File.\r\n\r\nIf i got back to instantsearch.js 2.0.2 everything is working fine without any Reference Errors.\r\n\r\nThats soooo strange :-(",
