    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "Yes i know, the problem is that our repository is a private project hosted on bitbucket.\r\nIts Laravel with Webpack and Laravel-mix like this:\r\n[Using Laravel Mix with webpack](https://scotch.io/tutorials/using-laravel-mix-with-webpack-for-all-your-assets)\r\nWe are using npm for all the node_modules packaging stuff. Thats our actual package.json:\r\n\r\n\"devDependencies\": {\r\n    \"axios\": \"^0.15.3\",\r\n    \"babel-core\": \"^6.26.0\",\r\n    \"babel-loader\": \"^7.1.3\",\r\n    \"bootstrap-sass\": \"^3.3.7\",\r\n    \"bulma-start\": \"0.0.2\",\r\n    \"cross-env\": \"^5.0.5\",\r\n    \"css-loader\": \"^0.27.3\",\r\n    \"laravel-mix\": \"^1.4.2\",\r\n    \"node-sass\": \"^4.7.2\",\r\n    \"sass-loader\": \"^6.0.6\",\r\n    \"style-loader\": \"^0.16.0\",\r\n    \"uglify-js\": \"^2.8.15\",\r\n    \"vue\": \"^2.5.13\",\r\n    \"vue-router\": \"^3.0.1\",\r\n    \"vue-select\": \"^2.4.0\",\r\n    \"vue-slider-component\": \"^2.5.8\",\r\n    \"vuex\": \"^3.0.1\",\r\n    \"webpack\": \"^3.11.0\",\r\n    \"webpack-hot-middleware\": \"^2.21.1\"\r\n  },\r\n  \"dependencies\": {\r\n    \"algoliasearch\": \"^3.24.12\",\r\n    \"blueimp-canvastoblob\": \"^2.1.0\",\r\n    \"blueimp-file-upload-npm\": \"^9.12.3\",\r\n    \"blueimp-load-image\": \"^2.18.0\",\r\n    \"blueimp-tmpl\": \"^3.11.0\",\r\n    \"bulma\": \"^0.6.2\",\r\n    \"canvas-to-blob\": \"0.0.0\",\r\n    \"clipboard\": \"^1.7.1\",\r\n    \"dropzone\": \"^4.3.0\",\r\n    \"font-awesome\": \"^4.7.0\",\r\n    \"instantsearch.js\": \"2.0.2\",\r\n    \"jquery\": \"3.2.1\",\r\n    \"jquery-datetime-picker\": \"^2.5.11\",\r\n    \"jquery-ui\": \"^1.12.1\",\r\n    \"jquery.ui.widget\": \"^1.10.3\",\r\n    \"modernizr\": \"^3.5.0\",\r\n    \"moment\": \"^2.20.1\",\r\n    \"nouislider\": \"^9.2.0\",\r\n    \"slick-carousel\": \"^1.8.1\",\r\n    \"sweetalert\": \"^1.1.3\",\r\n    \"tmpl\": \"^1.0.4\"\r\n  },\r\n\r\nOur webpack.mix.js is:\r\n\r\nconst mix = require('laravel-mix');\r\nconst webpack = require('webpack');\r\n\r\nconst extract = [\r\n    'jquery',\r\n    'sweetalert',\r\n    'instantsearch.js',\r\n    'slick-carousel'  \r\n];\r\n\r\nmix.autoload({\r\n    //instantsearch: ['instantsearch'],\r\n    jquery: ['$', 'jQuery', 'jquery']\r\n});\r\n\r\nand then comes all the mix.stuff like mix.sass/mix.copy/mix.js and so on\r\n\r\nOur app.js starts with:\r\n\r\nwindow.$ = require('jquery');\r\nrequire('bootstrap-sass');\r\nwindow.noUiSlider = require('nouislider');\r\nwindow.instantsearch = require('instantsearch.js');\r\n$(function(){ ...\r\n\r\nIf i change the line \"instantsearch.js\": \"2.0.2\" to \"instantsearch.js\": \"^2.0.2\" and make a npm update and the a npm run dev the compiling process is successful but if i reload the page in the browser i am getting Reference errors like \"ReferenceError: $ is not defined\" to this line \"$(function()\" in a different includes of our own JS Files.\r\n\r\nAnd on the Page with the Instantsearch we are getting the error the \"window.instantsearch isnt existing\" and so on. ",
